From 34e3b3391d852d79392a35ac760158d02133f6d8 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: FishSlayR Dev <dev@fishslayr.local>
Date: Sun, 5 Jul 2026 18:29:49 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Tournament mode step 2: publish path (tournament.js) + sync
 hooks

- src/lib/tournament.js: publish minimal catch projections to the active
  tournament (auto-publish + per-catch opt-out via tournOptOut), reusing the
  existing 640px photoThumb. Bass-photo guard mirrors the server trigger;
  rejected entries invalidate locally but keep the personal catch. Idempotent
  re-publish; owner-invalidation reconciled on pull.
- src/lib/sync.js: flushTournament() after the catch push, reconcileTournament()
  after the pull. Offline-first: failures stay pending and retry.
- test/publish_test.mjs: exercises the real lifecycle end-to-end.

Active-tournament state lives on the profile object (data.activeTournament =
{ tournamentId, teamId }) so it rides the existing profiles-row sync.
